## üîß Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

#### 1. Node Won't Start

**Symptom:** Clicking "Start Node" shows error or connection indicator stays red

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Check if zcashd is already running
ps aux | grep zcashd

# Kill existing process if found
killall zcashd

# Check zcashd exists
ls -la ~/zcash/src/zcashd

# Check configuration
cat ~/.zcash/zcash.conf

# Check logs
tail -f ~/.zcash/debug.log

# Try starting manually
~/zcash/src/zcashd

# Check for error messages
```

#### 2. RPC Connection Refused

**Symptom:** "Connection refused" errors when clicking commands

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Verify zcashd is running
ps aux | grep zcashd

# Check RPC port
netstat -an | grep 8232

# Verify config has RPC enabled
grep server ~/.zcash/zcash.conf

# Check RPC credentials match
grep rpcuser ~/.zcash/zcash.conf
grep rpcpassword ~/.zcash/zcash.conf

# Try manual RPC call
curl --user zcashgui:YOUR_PASSWORD \
  --data-binary '{"jsonrpc": "1.0", "id":"test", "method": "getinfo", "params": [] }' \
  -H 'content-type: text/plain;' \
  http://127.0.0.1:8232/
```

#### 3. Build Failed

**Symptom:** Installation stops during build phase

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Check available disk space
df -h

# Check available RAM
free -h

# Clean previous build
cd ~/zcash
./zcutil/clean.sh

# Update system
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade

# Install missing dependencies
sudo apt-get install build-essential pkg-config libc6-dev m4 g++-multilib autoconf libtool libncurses5-dev unzip git python3 zlib1g-dev wget bsdmainutils automake curl

# Try build again
./zcutil/build.sh -j$(nproc)

# If still fails, build with less cores
./zcutil/build.sh -j1
```

#### 4. Slow Sync

**Symptom:** Blockchain sync takes very long time

**Solutions:**

```conf
# Add to zcash.conf for faster sync
dbcache=4000        # Increase cache
maxconnections=125  # More peers
par=8               # More verification threads

# For SSD
disablewallet=1     # Disable wallet during initial sync
# Re-enable after sync complete
```

```bash
# Check sync progress
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli getblockchaininfo

# Monitor debug log
tail -f ~/.zcash/debug.log

# Check network connectivity
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli getnetworkinfo
```

#### 5. GUI Not Responding

**Symptom:** Interface freezes or becomes unresponsive

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Check Python version
python3 --version
# Should be 3.7+

# Check if tkinter is installed
python3 -c "import tkinter"

# Install tkinter if missing
# Ubuntu/Debian:
sudo apt-get install python3-tk

# macOS:
# Usually included with Python

# Check system resources
top
# Look for high CPU/RAM usage

# Restart the GUI
pkill -f zcash_manager.py
python3 zcash_manager.py
```

#### 6. Wallet Not Found

**Symptom:** Wallet operations fail with "wallet not found"

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Check if wallet exists
ls -la ~/.zcash/wallet.dat

# If missing, node needs to create it
# Stop node
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli stop

# Remove lock files
rm ~/.zcash/.lock
rm ~/.zcash/testnet3/.lock  # if testnet

# Start node - will create new wallet
~/zcash/src/zcashd

# Wait 30 seconds
sleep 30

# Check wallet created
ls -la ~/.zcash/wallet.dat

# IMPORTANT: New wallet = new addresses
# If you had old wallet, restore from backup
```

#### 7. Transaction Won't Confirm

**Symptom:** Sent transaction stays pending

**Solutions:**

```bash
# Check transaction status
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli gettransaction YOUR_TXID

# Check if in mempool
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli getmempoolinfo

# Check for operation status (shielded tx)
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli z_getoperationstatus

# Check sync status
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli getblockchaininfo

# If not synced, transaction won't propagate
# Wait for full sync

# Check network connections
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli getconnectioncount
# Should have >5 connections

# For stuck shielded operation
~/zcash/src/zcash-cli z_getoperationresult
```

### Getting Help

**Check Logs:**
```bash
# Main log file
tail -f ~/.zcash/debug.log

# Testnet log
tail -f ~/.zcash/testnet3/debug.log

# Search for errors
grep ERROR ~/.zcash/debug.log

# Last 100 lines
tail -100 ~/.zcash/debug.log
```

