## üìû Support

### Getting Help

**For Zcash Node Manager Issues:**
- GitHub Issues: [Create issue]
- Email: support@example.com

**For General Zcash Questions:**
- Community Forum: https://forum.zcashcommunity.com/
- Discord Support Channel: https://discord.gg/zcash
- Reddit: https://reddit.com/r/zec

**For Security Issues:**
- Email: security@example.com
- PGP Key: [Link to public key]
- Report privately first, public disclosure after fix

### FAQ

**Q: Is this official Zcash software?**
A: No, this is a community-developed GUI tool for managing Zcash nodes. It uses official Zcash software (zcashd) under the hood.

**Q: Can I use this on mainnet?**
A: Yes! The default configuration includes testnet for safety, but you can switch to mainnet by removing the testnet=1 line from zcash.conf.

**Q: Is my wallet secure?**
A: The wallet is as secure as your system. Follow security best practices: encrypt wallet, backup regularly, use strong passwords, keep system updated.

**Q: How long does initial sync take?**
A: Mainnet: 1-7 days depending on hardware/connection. Testnet: 4-24 hours. Regtest: instant.

**Q: Can I mine Zcash with this?**
A: CPU mining only works on testnet. Mainnet requires ASIC hardware and mining pools.

**Q: What's the difference between transparent and shielded?**
A: Transparent (t-addr) are like Bitcoin - public. Shielded (z-addr) are private - encrypted amounts and addresses.

**Q: Do I need to run my own node?**
A: Not required but recommended for privacy, security, and supporting the network.

**Q: Can I run multiple nodes?**
A: Yes, use different data directories with -datadir flag and different ports.

**Q: How do I upgrade Zcash?**
A: Pull latest code (git pull), rebuild (./zcutil/build.sh), restart node.

**Q: What if I lose my wallet?**
A: Your funds are lost forever. ALWAYS BACKUP YOUR WALLET.

